A. Linux only
B. Windows only
C. Both Windows and Linux
D. Cloud only

3. IDS architecture mainly consists of:
A. Sensors, manager, database
B. Router, switch, firewall
C. VPN, proxy, NAT
D. Client and server

4. IDS sensors are responsible for:
A. Blocking attacks
B. Monitoring and detecting activity
C. Encrypting packets
D. Load balancing

5. Bypassing an IDS means:
A. Disabling IDS
B. Evading detection mechanisms
C. Blocking traffic
D. Updating signatures

